Charles II. in 1661, created thirteen Baronets of Barbadoes;
              each of whom had in the island not less than a thousands pounds 
              a year, and some ten thousand pounds a year.

div.p:
In 1632, the English settled at Montserrat;
               and, in the same year, the Dutch settled at St.
               Eustasia.

There have ever beem, since our knowledge
                  of the East, two sorts of sugar made there;
                  raw or muscovado sugar, and sugar-candy;
                  the first used only for culinary purposes, and
                  the latter for every other purpose of diet, 
                  luxury, and exportation

