or hung up a chimney; or laid under the threshold of the door of the party, to suffer; with incantation songs, or curses, performed at midnight, regarding the aspects of the moon. The party who wants to do the mischief, is also sent to the burying-grounds, or some secret place, where spirits are supposed to frequent, to invoke his dead parent to assist him in the curse.

In general, Obi-men are more sagacious than Obi-women, in giving, or taking away diseases;
